// Resource script for unit-test binaries on Windows.
//
// `tauri-build` ships a Common-Controls v6 manifest with the production
// exe, but cargo only embeds resources into binaries enumerated in
// `embed_resource::compile_for(...)`. Test exes therefore default to
// comctl32 v5, which lacks `TaskDialogIndirect` — and the resulting
// `STATUS_ENTRYPOINT_NOT_FOUND` (0xC0000139) appears the moment the
// loader resolves `tauri-runtime-wry`'s dialog imports.
//
// We sidestep that by compiling a tiny .rc whose only payload is the
// same v6 manifest, and asking `embed_resource::compile_for_tests` to
// link it into every `--test` binary the workspace builds.
//
// Reference:
//   tauri-build-2.5.6/src/windows-app-manifest.xml (canonical source)
//   embed-resource-3.0.9/src/lib.rs (compile_for_tests)

#define RT_MANIFEST 24
1 RT_MANIFEST "test-manifest.xml"
